<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: page box properties</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#page-box-page-rule"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="paged" />
  <meta name="assert" content="The 'width' and 'height' properties do not apply to a page box."/>
  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
   @page  { 
		width: 1in;
		height: 1in;
		border: 2pt solid black;
	}
	div.biggerBox {
		width: 2in;
		height: 2in;
		border: 1pt solid black;
	}
  ]]></style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <div>When printed, this page should have a black border. The area inside the border should be larger than 1in x 1in. The box below should be 2&quot;x2&quot; and fit on the page.</div>
  <div class="biggerBox"></div>
 </body>
</html>